      <p>It is intended for <strong>informational and personal planning purposes only</strong>.</p>
      
      <h2>2. What DhanRakshak Is Not</h2>
      <p>DhanRakshak is <strong>not</strong> any of the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>A <strong>payment processor</strong> — the app does not process, facilitate, or execute any financial transactions</li>
        <li>A <strong>lending or credit service</strong> — the app does not offer loans, credit lines, or any form of borrowing</li>
        <li>A <strong>cryptocurrency or investment platform</strong> — the app does not facilitate trading, investing, or holding of any digital or traditional financial assets</li>
        <li>A <strong>licensed financial advisor</strong> — the app does not provide personalized financial, tax, legal, or investment advice</li>
        <li>A <strong>banking or wallet service</strong> — the app does not hold, store, or transfer money on your behalf</li>
      </ul>
      <p>DhanRakshak is purely a <strong>tracker and planner</strong>. It helps you record, categorize, and understand your personal financial data. Any financial decisions you make based on information displayed in the app are <strong>entirely your own responsibility</strong>.</p>
      
      <h2>3. No Financial Advice Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>The information displayed in DhanRakshak — including analytics, budgets, spending trends, and savings projections — is provided for <strong>general informational purposes only</strong> and does not constitute financial, investment, tax, or legal advice.</p>
      <p>You should consult a qualified professional before making any financial decisions. DhanRakshak and its developers <strong>are not responsible for any financial outcomes</strong> resulting from your use of the app.</p>
      
      <h2>4. User Responsibility</h2>
      <p>You are responsible for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Ensuring the accuracy</strong> of data you enter into the app</li>
        <li><strong>Reviewing imported data</strong> from bank statements or third-party integrations</li>
        <li><strong>Protecting access</strong> to your device and accounts</li>
        <li><strong>Complying with applicable laws</strong> when using the app</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>5. Third-Party Integrations</h2>
      <p>The app may integrate with third-party services such as <strong>Splitwise</strong> and <strong>Google Sign-In</strong>.</p>
      <p>When you connect such services:</p>
